    "summary": "Consumer discretionary businesses are levered to the highs and lows of economic cycles. This sensitive demand profile can cause the industry to underperform when macro uncertainty enters the fray, and over the past six months, its 3.8% return has fallen short of the S&P 500’s 6.3% gain.",
